Kilifi North MP Gedeon Mung&rsquo;aro has intensified campaigns for his governor bid.He has vowed to sell the controversial Sh140 million beachfront mansion acquired by Governor Amason Kingi if elected. Mung&rsquo;aro said he will also sell the chopper alleged to have been bought by the governor.Speaking in Chakama Malindi subcounty on Friday, he said the mansion bought by Kingi was a waste of taxpayers&rsquo; money.Mung&rsquo;aro said he will invest the proceeds in development projects. &ldquo;I&rsquo;ll be staying at [my] home in Dabaso. No need to retain such a facility, which costs taxpayers huge sums of money,&rsquo;&rsquo; he said.Mung&rsquo;aro accused the Kingi administration of abetting corruption, instead of investing in irrigation.